The Charlatan can take <PRO_HISHER> schemes to a next level and really embody a character to outsmart others. This ability can be used once per day and gives the Charlatan a 10% chance (maximum of 50% at level 10) of successfully act as a specialist Fighter of the same level (up to level 13), gaining the benefits of specialization with whatever weapon <PRO_HESHE> is wielding, a Warrior's Thac0 and APR and raise <PRO_HISHER> Strength to 18/50 during 5 rounds.

There's also a 5% chance that the act will fail miserably making the Charlatan Frustrated, giving <PRO_HIMHER> a -3 penalty to Thac0, damage, Armor Class and saving throws. During the act, obviously, the Charlatan can't cast spells, sing <PRO_HISHER> Bard Song or use special abilities. Both effects can be dispelled.~
